# GeoIP Country Blocking Configuration
# 
# This file contains country codes to block using IPdeny zone files.
# Each line should contain a two-letter country code (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2).
# Lines starting with # are comments.
#
# To use this configuration:
# 1. Copy this file to geoip-countries.conf
# 2. Uncomment or add country codes you wish to block
# 3. Run: sudo /path/to/update-geoip-simple.sh
#
# To find country codes causing issues on your server:
# - Check fail2ban logs: sudo fail2ban-client status
# - Analyze auth logs: sudo grep "Failed password" /var/log/auth.log
# - Use the analyze script: sudo ./analyze-attacks.sh
